# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: StoryBeginnings | Scene: DayOfTheFuneral
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "The day of King Orwell's funeral has arrived."
    new "The day of King Orwell's funeral has arrived."

    old "A week has passed since his body was found."
    new "A week has passed since his body was found."

    old "In attendance are all the great houses and families of Rosanna, come to pay their final respects."
    new "In attendance are all the great houses and families of Rosanna, come to pay their final respects."

    old "Beloved in life and beloved in death, a nation mourns the passing of their king."
    new "Beloved in life and beloved in death, a nation mourns the passing of their king."

    old "Sarah looks out over the crowd of people that have fitted themselves into the great hall."
    new "Sarah looks out over the crowd of people that have fitted themselves into the great hall."

    old "Sarah..."
    new "Sarah..."

    old "Thomas embraces his sister."
    new "Thomas embraces his sister."

    old "Who would have wanted to hurt Dad?"
    new "Who would have wanted to hurt Dad?"

    old "Sarah can't find the will to hug him back."
    new "Sarah can't find the will to hug him back."

    old "It's okay Thomas, we just need to get through today. Let those questions rest for another day."
    new "It's okay Thomas, we just need to get through today. Let those questions rest for another day."

    old "Then what?"
    new "Then what?"

    old "Thomas sounded exasperated."
    new "Thomas sounded exasperated."

    old "Then another day. Coronation. Another day. On and on, Thomas. We just need to keep moving forward. Dad might not be here anymore, but he's watching over us."
    new "Then another day. Coronation. Another day. On and on, Thomas. We just need to keep moving forward. Dad might not be here anymore, but he's watching over us."

    old "Sarah turns to her brother, looking deep into his eyes. His eyes are bloodshot from the crying that he hides from her."
    new "Sarah turns to her brother, looking deep into his eyes. His eyes are bloodshot from the crying that he hides from her."

    old "We need to make him proud now. Remember: composure."
    new "We need to make him proud now. Remember: composure."

    old "Thomas turns away from her, staring off into the distance, trying to look at nothing at all."
    new "Thomas turns away from her, staring off into the distance, trying to look at nothing at all."

    old "Sarah tries to remember the week since her father's death."
    new "Sarah tries to remember the week since her father's death."

    old "She had to do so much, in a way, it spared her from dealing with her grief."
    new "She had to do so much, in a way, it spared her from dealing with her grief."

    old "Invitations, decorations, preparations. An endless amount of work for her to lose herself in."
    new "Invitations, decorations, preparations. An endless amount of work for her to lose herself in."

    old "Thomas, on the other hand, had turned inwards. He had grown more somber, and she had found him on some nights, walking through the dark unlit castle halls."
    new "Thomas, on the other hand, had turned inwards. He had grown more somber, and she had found him on some nights, walking through the dark unlit castle halls."

    old "Sarah made a mental note, she needed to talk to her brother. It pained her to admit it, but he wasn't strong. He needed to know he could lean on her."
    new "Sarah made a mental note, she needed to talk to her brother. It pained her to admit it, but he wasn't strong. He needed to know he could lean on her."

    old "The events of the day proceeded. Priests read out the last rites. Some spoke words of comfort."
    new "The events of the day proceeded. Priests read out the last rites. Some spoke words of comfort."

    old "Not before long, Sarah and Thomas found themselves in the middle of the great hall, walking in linked arms, floating from one group of nobles to the next."
    new "Not before long, Sarah and Thomas found themselves in the middle of the great hall, walking in linked arms, floating from one group of nobles to the next."

    old "Nobleman\" \"Our condolences."
    new "Nobleman\" \"Our condolences."

    old "Noblewoman\" \"He was a great man."
    new "Noblewoman\" \"He was a great man."

    old "Ambassador\" \"He will be missed."
    new "Ambassador\" \"He will be missed."

    old "Sarah didn't want to sound cynical, she was sure that many of them truly meant what they said. It just seemed like words, not just these words but all words, seemed so empty right now."
    new "Sarah didn't want to sound cynical, she was sure that many of them truly meant what they said. It just seemed like words, not just these words but all words, seemed so empty right now."

    old "Soon, she found herself subjected to a torrent of sympathies. It all became too much."
    new "Soon, she found herself subjected to a torrent of sympathies. It all became too much."

    old "Thomas, I need to take a moment, please carry on without me."
    new "Thomas, I need to take a moment, please carry on without me."

    old "Sarah unlinked her arm from her brother and quickly walked away."
    new "Sarah unlinked her arm from her brother and quickly walked away."

    old "Fresh air, that's what she needed."
    new "Fresh air, that's what she needed."

